  "response": "You can find the audiobook of \"Beowulf\" translated by Burton Raffel on various platforms. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n1. **Audible**: They often have a wide selection of audiobooks, including classic literature.\n2. **Google Play Books**: This platform also offers audiobooks for purchase.\n3. **Apple Books**: If you're an Apple user, you can check their store for audiobooks.\n4. **Library Services**: Check your local library's digital resources. Many libraries partner with services like OverDrive or Libby, where you can borrow audiobooks for free with a library card.\n\nMake sure to check the availability and any subscription or purchase options.",
